articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israeli military strikes killed at least 30 Palestinians overnight in the Gaza Strip, most of them in the Nuseirat camp at the centre of the enclave, medics said after some tanks pulled back from an area they had raided.
articles.title: Israeli tanks retreat from central Gaza camp, medics say 30 killed

articles.author: John Irish, Tom Balmforth
articles.description: NATO diplomats say there is no consensus among alliance members to invite Ukraine.
articles.title: Ukraine asks NATO for membership invite next week, letter shows

articles.author: Graham Fahy, Padraic Halpin, Conor Humphries
articles.description: Ireland's main opposition party Sinn Fein looked on course to narrowly win the most votes at a general election on Friday, but its two main centre-right rivals will likely have enough seats to govern again without it, an exit poll showed.
articles.title: Sinn Fein tops Irish exit poll, but coalition parties look set for re-election

articles.author: Maya Gebeily
articles.description: Syrian rebels opposed to President Bashar al-Assad said on Friday they had reached the heart of the northern city of Aleppo, after a surprise sweep through government-held towns and nearly a decade after having been forced out of the city.
articles.title: Syria rebels say they reached Aleppo city in surprise sweep

articles.author: Sarah Young, Alistair Smout
articles.description: Britain's parliament voted in favour of a new bill to legalise assisted dying on Friday, opening the way for months of further debate on an issue that has divided the country and raised questions about the standard of palliative care.
articles.title: British lawmakers give initial support to assisted dying bill

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un told Russian defence minister Ukraine's use of long-range weapons is the result of direct military intervention by the United States and Moscow is entitled to take action in self-defence, state media said on Saturday.
articles.title: North Korea leader Kim: Russia has right to exercise self defence against Ukraine

articles.author: David Lewis, John Irish
articles.description: A French plan to significantly reduce its military presence in West and central Africa risks backfiring and further diminishing the former colonial power's influence in the region at a time when Russia is gaining ground.
articles.title: France on the back foot in Africa after Chadian snub

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The head of Hezbollah, Naim Qassem, pledged on Friday to coordinate closely with the Lebanese army to implement a ceasefire deal with Israel, which he said his group had agreed to "with heads held high".
articles.title: Hezbollah chief pledges to coordinate with army to implement truce

articles.author: Felix Light
articles.description: Pro-European Union Georgians were gathering on Friday for a second night of protests, after the country's ruling party said on Thursday that it was halting EU accession talks until 2028, in an abrupt freeze to a long-standing national aim.
articles.title: Pro-EU Georgians gather for second night of protests against accession freeze

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: French President Emmanuel Macron reaffirmed his support for Ukraine and reiterated his condemnation of an escalation in Russia's attacks against the country in a phone call with Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskiy, said the two leaders.
articles.title: France's Macron reaffirms support for Ukraine in call with Zelenskiy
